<!-- 03 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01 — About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">The washer breakdown is never convenient. We know.</h2>

        <p>A washing machine going out means laundry piling up, a trip to the laundromat, and — if you live in an apartment or condo — the particular stress of a broken stackable unit crammed into a closet that barely fits one person, let alone a technician with tools.</p>

        <p>Washer calls are one of the higher-volume repairs we run in LA. The city has an enormous rental stock — Silver Lake bungalows, West Hollywood high-rises, Culver City condos, Pasadena craftsmans — and most of them have either a stackable unit in a laundry closet or a front-loader in a utility space that gets harder use than manufacturers typically account for. Our technicians know the configurations, the brands common in LA housing, and what fails first on each of them.</p>

        <p>We carry parts on the van. For the Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Bosch, and Miele units that make up the majority of LA washer calls, we can usually complete the repair on the first visit. No "we need to order the part" — unless it's something genuinely unusual.</p>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <div class="tip-label">🏢 Stackable &amp; Condo Units</div>
          <p>A significant portion of washer calls in LA involve stackable units in closets or laundry alcoves with minimal clearance. Working in tight spaces requires the right approach — our technicians come prepared for it and won't ask you to clear a path for a dolly. If you have a stacked unit, let us know when you call so we send the right technician with the right tools.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-box-blue">
          <div class="tip-label">🌀 Front-Load Mold Note</div>
          <p>Front-load washers in LA apartments with limited ventilation are prone to mold and odor buildup on the door gasket. It's not a major repair, but it's worth addressing — a torn or mold-saturated gasket can also cause water leaks. We inspect the gasket on every front-load service call.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
        <div class="cta-label">Same Day Washer Repair</div>
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="cta-phone">{phone}</a>
        <a href={`tel:${phoneRaw}`} class="btn-cta">Call Now — We Pick Up</a>
        <a href="/book" class="btn-cta" style="background:#222; margin-top:-4px;">Book Online</a>
        <div class="cta-sub">Mon–Fri 7am–9pm · Sat 8am–7pm · Sun 9am–5pm</div>
        <hr class="cta-divider" />
        <ul class="cta-detail">
          <li>$89 diagnostic — applied to repair</li>
          <li>90-day warranty on parts &amp; labor</li>
          <li>OEM parts for all major brands</li>
