<!-- 10 FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">08 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Washer repair — what people ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does washer repair cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair the moment you approve the work. Most washer repairs in LA run between $130 and $350 depending on the part and brand. Drain pump and lid switch replacements are on the lower end. Control board or motor issues on premium brands like Miele or Bosch run higher. We give you a full written estimate before any work begins — what we quote is what appears on the invoice.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can you repair my washer the same day in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Yes. We have technicians running washer calls across LA daily. Call before noon and we can typically be there that afternoon. We stock parts for the brands and models we see most often in LA — Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, Miele, Bosch — so most repairs are completed on the first visit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair stackable washers in apartments and condos?</h3>
        <p>Yes — stackable units in closets and laundry alcoves are one of the most common washer calls we get in LA. Working in a tight laundry closet requires a specific approach. Our technicians come prepared for it: the right tools, the right sequence for accessing components without damaging cabinetry, and experience with the brands commonly found in LA condos — LG, Electrolux, Bosch, Samsung.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My front-load washer smells like mold — can you fix that?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Front-load washers in LA apartments with limited ventilation are prone to mold buildup on the rubber door gasket. We clean the drum and gasket, inspect for tears or deterioration that trap water, and check whether the door seal needs replacement. We also look at the drain path to make sure residual water isn't sitting where it shouldn't be.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My washer won't drain — what's usually wrong?</h3>
        <p>The drain pump is the most common culprit, especially if you hear the motor running but water stays in the drum. It could also be a clogged pump filter — on front-loaders, this is the small access panel near the bottom front of the machine, and it's frequently neglected. A blocked drain hose or a faulty lid switch on top-loaders are also common. Our technicians diagnose before replacing parts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does the 90-day warranty cover on washer repairs?</h3>
        <p>Our 90-day warranty covers both the part and the labor on every repair we complete. If the same issue returns within that period, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair high-efficiency (HE) and commercial washers?</h3>
        <p>Yes. High-efficiency front-load and top-load washers are the majority of what we service in LA. For commercial washers — laundromat units, multi-family building machines, hotel laundry — our commercial diagnostic fee is $120. We work on Speed Queen, Electrolux Professional, and other commercial-grade brands.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

